              "content": "---\ndescription: Physics and ML benchmark suite rules\nglobs: benchmarks/**/*\nalwaysApply: false\n---\n\n# Benchmark conventions\n\nPlan: `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-14-benchmarks-and-simulations.md`\n\n## Before timing\n\n1. Shared `params.toml` across li and reference impls (C++, Rust, Julia, Python)\n2. `verify.py` must pass (energy drift, momentum, trajectory hash)\n3. **`lic build` must pass Lean** on all `benchmarks/tier2_physics/` li sources\n4. Document flags: `lic --release --verified`, Clang `-O3 -march=native`\n\n## Tiers\n\n| Tier | Examples |\n|------|----------|\n| 0 | compile-time shape traps |\n| 2 | `three_body`, `md_lennard_jones`, PDE stencils |\n| 3 | `mlp_forward`, MNIST subset |\n\n## Reporting\n\n- CSV columns: `benchmark, lang, threads, metric, value, unit, cpu_model, flags`\n- Label BLAS/NumPy/PyTorch columns explicitly — never compare naive Python to SIMD li without labeling\n- Regression: investigate if li > 1.2× C++ on Tier 1–2 on the same machine\n- **Social:** run `./scripts/plot_shareables.sh` before posting benchmark or CI results to X\n\nPlot spec: `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-14-plots-and-social.md`\n\n## Reference impls\n\nEach Tier 2+ benchmark needs a C++ reference that passes `verify.py` before li numbers are published.\n\n## tier5_http (li-httpd / `lis`)\n\nConfig lives in **TOML only** (`benchmarks/tier5_http/`). Do not hardcode scenarios in Python.\n\n- Merge: `defaults.toml` ← `scenarios/*/bench.toml`\n- Harness: `verify_http.py`, `bench_http.py`, `exploit_http.py`, `audit_nginx_src.py`\n- CI: `lis/scripts/verify-http.sh`\n",
