          "text": "The benchmarks repository contains a reference to `run-tier5-http-bench.sh`.\n\nThe lic repo requires the harness scaffold, which will include creating several modules and files such as `http_bench_toml.py`, `bench_http.py`, `verify_http.py`, and `plot_http.py`, along with TOML config files, nginx template, shell scripts, documentation, and schema definitions.\n\nUpdate plan frontmatter for bench-harness completed. The shell script `li-tests/tier5_http/run_harness_smoke.sh` is used for running harness smoke tests, or it can be added to `run_httpd_config`. A unit test file `li-tests/tier5_http/test_http_bench_toml.py` will be added to test merge logic.\n\nThe design for `bench_http.py` avoids hardcoded scenarios by resolving them dynamically from configuration files instead of hardcoding values like `[\"static_small\", \"static_large\"]`. For verification in CI without nginx, the `ci` profile sets `timing=false`.\n\nverify_http.py validates merged config and generates fixtures, skipping runtime HTTP checks in CI when nginx is absent. In CI, it parses and validates TOML, renders nginx.conf, and skips HTTP checks to avoid flakiness.\n\nThe verification process includes structural checks like required keys and enabled flags, and runtime checks when nginx is present or when using stub static handler. Load and timing checks occur only when timing is enabled and wrk is available, with synthetic data in dry-run mode. The implementation starts with http_bench_toml.py, followed by bench_http.py and verify_http.py. The nginx.conf.in template will be created next.\n\nThe nginx configuration template uses placeholders for worker processes, port, and document root, with simple string replacement from the merged TOML server section.\n\nFor fixture generation, the system reads default values from `[fixtures.static_1k]` and creates files with random or zero bytes, ensuring SHA256 checksums match between generated files and bench.toml entries. However, a chicken-and-egg problem exists where fixture generation depends on checksums that are also generated during the process.\n\nA better approach for static_small uses `body_len = 1024` in bench.toml instead of `body_sha256` in CI environments.",
